    <p align="left" class="PageHeader"><img src="/rt/Dingbats/Divider.A.512.gif" width="512" height="8"  /></p>
    <p align="left" class="PageHeader">Product Replacement Policy</p>
    <p align="left" class="PageHeader"><img src="/rt/Dingbats/Divider.Z.512.gif" width="512" height="8"  /></p>
    <p align="left"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">If your copy of a product is lost or destroyed (for example if your hard drive crashes) Perfect Sync will   replace it at no charge.&nbsp; The replacement product will be keyed to use the same   Authorization Code as the original.</span></p>
    <p align="left"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">This policy is limited to one replacement per licensee per product.&nbsp; If you need additional replacements,   there will be a 15%-of-original-cost charge for each subsequent   copy.</span> If losing it the first time didn't teach you how important backups are, that's not our problem.</p>
    <p align="left"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">To request a product   replacement, simply send an email message to <a href="/pp/Company/ContactUs.php">Perfect Sync Customer Support</a>.&nbsp;   For security reasons <em>you must include your Perfect Sync Authorization Code in   your message</em>.&nbsp; Perfect Sync <em>will not replace a product if you don't know   your Authorization Code</em> so be sure to store your Authorization Code in your   permanent (paper) files.</span></p>
    <!-- InstanceEndEditable -->
</div>
